Class VaccineArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • VaccineArray
  • public class VaccineArray
extends java.lang.Object
    Class used to create and populate a Vaccine array of objects using the data from vaccinations.csv and use this array to find certain Vaccine objects given a specific country and date combination. 01/03/2022

      • addVax

        public void addVax​(Vaccine v)
        Method used by VaccineArrayApp to populate the vaccines array of objects after the data in vaccinations.csv is extracted and separated accordingly.
        Parameters:
        v - Vaccine object to add to the vaccines array.

      • findVax

        public Vaccine findVax​(Vaccine v)
        Method used to find a Vaccine object in the vaccines array with the country and date combination in v and to then return this object in the array.
        Parameters:
        v - Vaccine object whose country and date combination is compared to elements in the vaccines array to determine whether it is in the array.
        Returns:
        the Vaccine object from the vaccines array if it is found; null if it not found.

      • outputVax

        public java.lang.String[] outputVax​(java.lang.String[] countries,
                                    java.lang.String date,
                                    int count)
        Method used to formulate output to be produced after the user provides input and the vaccines array is searched accordingly.
        Parameters:
        countries - Array containing the list of countries entered by the user.
        date - String containing the date inputted by the user.
        count - Gives the number of countries contained in the countries array.
        Returns:
        String array containing the vaccination quantities for the given country and date combinations, appending "Not found" where it wasn't located in the vaccines array.
